---

🏗️ STEP 1 — Build your “Golden SNO Cluster”

This is the most important step.

👉 Install one SNO normally (Agent / ISO / UPI — your choice)

Then configure EVERYTHING you want baked into all future clusters:

🔧 Must include:

Pull secret pointing to your mirror

ICSP / IDMS (mirror configs)

Operators (from your mirrored catalog)

Storage / network configs

Any base apps


👉 Example things you already worked on:

IDMS (ImageDigestMirrorSet)

ITMS (if used)

Local registry (quay or custom)



---

📦 STEP 2 — Install Lifecycle Agent (LCA)

On that running cluster:

oc apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openshift-kni/lifecycle-agent/main/config/install.yaml

Verify:

oc get pods -n openshift-lifecycle-agent


---

🧱 STEP 3 — Create Seed Image

Now generate the reusable image.

Create Image CR

apiVersion: lca.openshift.io/v1
kind: SeedGenerator
metadata:
  name: seedimage
spec:
  image: <your-registry>/seed/sno:latest

Apply:

oc apply -f seed.yaml


---

What happens here:

Cluster snapshot is taken

Stored as OCI image

Pushed to your local registry (mirror)


👉 This is key for disconnected:

> Your seed image lives inside your mirror registry ✅




---

📀 STEP 4 — Create Installation ISO

On your bastion:

openshift-install image-based create image \
  --seed-image <your-registry>/seed/sno:latest \
  --dir ./ib-install

This generates:

rhcos-live.x86_64.iso



---

⚙️ STEP 5 — Create Node-specific Config

Each node still needs identity.

Create install-config.yaml (minimal now):

apiVersion: v1
baseDomain: example.com
metadata:
  name: sno1
pullSecret: '<your-mirror-pull-secret>'
sshKey: 'ssh-rsa AAAA...'

Then generate config ISO:

openshift-install image-based create config-image \
  --dir ./ib-install


---

🖥️ STEP 6 — Deploy New Node

Boot target server with:

Installation ISO

Config ISO


👉 Process:

1. Boot


2. Disk gets flashed with seed image


3. Config applied


4. Certificates regenerated


5. Cluster comes up



⏱️ ~10–15 minutes typically


---

🔄 STEP 7 — What happens internally (important)

lca-cli writes image → disk

recert regenerates:

API certs

kubeconfig

node identity


Cluster becomes unique


👉 So no conflicts even though same base image


---

🧠 HOW THIS FITS YOUR MIRROR SETUP

This is the part most people miss 👇

✅ Your mirror is reused automatically if:

Your seed cluster already had:

IDMS / ICSP configured

Operators installed from mirror


👉 Then:

> Every new cluster ALSO uses your mirror — no extra work




---

🔥 Important rule

👉 Whatever is in seed cluster = present in all new clusters

So:

Component	Must be in seed?

Release images	✅ Yes
Operator catalogs	✅ Yes
IDMS/ICSP	✅ Yes
Custom CA certs	✅ Yes



---

⚠️ Common mistakes (you should avoid)

❌ Mistake 1: Seed without mirror config

→ New cluster tries internet → FAIL


---

❌ Mistake 2: Adding operators later

→ defeats purpose

👉 Install operators BEFORE creating seed image


---

❌ Mistake 3: Wrong registry path

→ mismatch between seed + mirror


